In .NET MAUI, use `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` and the `RequestedThemeChanged` event:

```csharp
// Read current system theme
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current!.RequestedTheme;

// React to system theme changes in real time
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to {newTheme}");
    // Update UI or refresh styles here
};
```

**Force a specific theme** by setting `UserAppTheme`, which overrides the system setting:

```csharp
// Lock to dark mode regardless of system setting
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Lock to light mode
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Light;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

**XAML-side**, use `AppThemeBinding` so controls adapt automatically:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}" />
```

Key points:
- `RequestedTheme` — read-only, reflects the OS setting.
- `UserAppTheme` — read/write, overrides the OS setting. Set to `AppTheme.Unspecified` to follow the system again.
- `RequestedThemeChanged` fires when the **system** theme changes (even if `UserAppTheme` is set, your UI won't change unless `UserAppTheme` is `Unspecified`).
